text: Jaca Cathedral (also known as Cathedral of St Peter the Apostle), is the Roman Catholic cathedral of the Diocese of Jaca. It is in Jaca, Huesca, Spain. This is the first Romanesque cathedral built in Aragon (1070s-early 12th century).
